# Add Annotation to Document

This API endpoint allows you to delete an annotation from a specific document within a file cabinet.

## Request

To delete the annotation, make an HTTP POST request to the following URL: `{{ServerUrl}}/{{Platform}}/FileCabinets/{{FileCabinetId}}/Documents/{{DocumentId}}/Annotation`.

### Request Body

The request body should be in JSON format and include the following payload:

``` json
{
  "Annotations": [
    {
      "PageNumber": 0,
      "SectionNumber": 0,
      "AnnotationsPlacement": {
        "Items": [
          {
            "$type": "",
            "Layer": [
              {
                "Id": "",
                "Items": [
                  {
                    "$type": "",
                    "Id": ""
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
}

 ```

### Request Parameters

- `ServerUrl`: The URL of the server hosting the file cabinet.

- `Platform`: The platform on which the file cabinet is hosted.

- `FileCabinetId`: The ID of the file cabinet containing the document.

- `DocumentId`: The ID of the document.


## Response

Upon successful execution of the request, the API will return a response with a status code of 200 and the details of the created annotation in JSON format.

### Response Body

``` json
{
  "Annotations": [
    {
      "Annotation": [
        {
          "Items": [
            {
              "$type": "",
              "Location": {
                "Left": 0,
                "Top": 0,
                "Width": 0,
                "Height": 0
              },
              "Filled": true,
              "Ellipse": true,
              "Created": {
                "User": "",
                "Time": ""
              },
              "Color": "",
              "Rotation": 0,
              "Transparent": true,
              "StrokeWidth": 0,
              "Id": ""
            }
          ],
          "Id": 0
        }
      ],
      "SectionNumber": 0,
      "PageNumber": 0
    }
  ]
}

 ```

